            <div type="essay">
                <head type="title">Welcome</head>
                <p><hi rend="italic">The Early Ruskin Manuscripts, 1826&#x2013;1842</hi> is an archive of the youthful writing of John Ruskin (1819&#x2013;1900). 
                    When complete, <hi rend="italic">ERM</hi> will present a comprehensive diplomatic edition of Ruskin&#x02BC;s early
                    writing paired with facsimiles of the manuscripts. The documentary record is distinguished by 
                    its extraordinary quality and range, 
                    providing a substantial resource for study of an early Victorian British education. <hi rend="italic">ERM</hi> will therefore prove valuable to
                    scholars of Victorian culture and education generally, as well as to students of Ruskin in particular.
                </p>
                <p>For a detailed explanation of the archive's organization, consult 
                    <ref type="note" subtype="bibliographical" target="plan_of_archive_note.html">The Plan of the Archive</ref>. 
                    Justification of the archive's organization and contents is offered in 
                    <ref type="note" subtype="bibliographical" target="editorial_rationale_note.html">Editorial and Encoding Rationale and Methodology</ref>.
                </p>
                
                
            </div>
